{"title":"Use Apple’s Find My… Bike with the New AirBell for AirTag","link":"https://bikerumor.com/apple-find-my-bike-airbell-bike-bell-airtag/","date":1683036099000,"content":"<p>What if there was a bike bell that could possibly help you get your stolen bike back? Even if you don’t use a bell on your bike, you might want to rethink that stance. Introducing the AirBell. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>This <a href=\"https://apac.airbell.bike/products/airbell\" target=\"_blank\">unique bell</a> discreetly and ingeniously hides an Apple AirTag inside utilizing the Apple Find My network to help you get your bike back. </p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/AirBell-and-Airtag-exploded-view-e1681238304664.jpeg\"><img width=\"800\" height=\"611\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/AirBell-and-Airtag-exploded-view-e1681238304664-800x611.jpeg\" alt=\"AirBell and Airtag exploded view\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/AirBell-and-Airtag-exploded-view-e1681238304664-800x611.jpeg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/AirBell-and-Airtag-exploded-view-e1681238304664-297x227.jpeg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/AirBell-and-Airtag-exploded-view-e1681238304664-120x92.jpeg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/AirBell-and-Airtag-exploded-view-e1681238304664-768x586.jpeg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/AirBell-and-Airtag-exploded-view-e1681238304664.jpeg 1273w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>The bell completely hides the fact that it carries an AirTag. It also does so without impeding the bell’s ability to be a bell. Even with the AirTag installed the bell still has a ring that measures 85db.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure>\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/AirBell-with-installation-tool.jpeg\"><img width=\"720\" height=\"480\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/AirBell-with-installation-tool.jpeg\" alt=\"AirBell with installation tool\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/AirBell-with-installation-tool.jpeg 720w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/AirBell-with-installation-tool-297x198.jpeg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/AirBell-with-installation-tool-120x80.jpeg 120w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/AirBell-on-bar.jpeg\"><img width=\"720\" height=\"480\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/AirBell-on-bar.jpeg\" alt=\"AirBell on bar\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/AirBell-on-bar.jpeg 720w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/AirBell-on-bar-297x198.jpeg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/AirBell-on-bar-120x80.jpeg 120w\" /></a></figure>\n</figure>\n\n\n\n<p>The AirBell’s 22mm bar mount is made of a rugged fiber-reinforced plastic that sports an aluminum bell housing. The installation tool also comes with the purchase of the bell, so you can quickly add the bell to any one of your bikes.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/AirBell-with-Apple-AirTag-installed.jpeg\"><img width=\"800\" height=\"600\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/AirBell-with-Apple-AirTag-installed-800x600.jpeg\" alt=\"AirBell with Apple AirTag installed\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/AirBell-with-Apple-AirTag-installed-800x600.jpeg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/AirBell-with-Apple-AirTag-installed-297x223.jpeg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/AirBell-with-Apple-AirTag-installed-120x90.jpeg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/AirBell-with-Apple-AirTag-installed-768x576.jpeg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/AirBell-with-Apple-AirTag-installed.jpeg 1280w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>From their website; “<em>The Apple AirTag is the most popular tracker for bikes, eBikes, scooters, and e-scooters. Over 100,000 AirBells have been sold to date</em>.” The site also claims that they are the “<em>#1 bestselling bicycle accessory on Amazon</em>“.</p>\n\n\n\n<h2>AirBell Retail &amp; Feature Summary</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>Retail: $35 (on sale for $25 as of the writing of this article)</p>\n\n\n\n<ul>\n<li>Compatible with Apple AirTags (not included)</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Registered Design</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Inconspicuous</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Easy installation with an included tool (small flathead screwdriver) included</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Loudness rated at 85db</li>\n</ul>\n\n\n\n<p><em><a href=\"https://apac.airbell.bike/\" target=\"_blank\">Apac.AirBell.bike</a></em></p>\n<p>The post <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/apple-find-my-bike-airbell-bike-bell-airtag/\">Use Apple’s Find My… Bike with the New AirBell for AirTag</a> appeared first on <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com\">Bikerumor</a>.</p>","author":"Ron Frazelle","siteTitle":"Bikerumor","siteHash":"49f427af0a926f4232eb837006841d7242e153e3afbb590f32e4b104ea3e2718","entryHash":"77da78cb5e781d516c6d67464c7e2b98edb06edd1e78001f49ce2268c9945885","category":"Cycling"}